#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[!meta title=\"Converting dangerous documents to safe PDFs using Dangerzone\"]]\n"
msgstr "[[!meta title=\"Convertire documenti pericolosi in PDF sicuri con Dangerzone\"]]\n"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"When you receive untrusted documents, for example, email attachments, "
"*[Dangerzone](https://dangerzone.rocks/)* allows you to convert them into "
"safe PDFs before opening."
msgstr ""
"Quando ricevi documenti non affidabili, ad esempio allegati di posta "
"elettronica, *[Dangerzone] (https://dangerzone.rocks/)* consente di "
"convertirli in PDF sicuri prima di aprirli."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Dangerzone* is particularly useful for journalists who might receive dangerous\n"
"documents from anonymous sources or download them from the Internet.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Dangerzone* è particolarmente utile per i giornalisti che potrebbero ricevere documenti\n"
"pericolosi da fonti anonime o scaricarli da Internet.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<div class=\"tip\">\n"
msgstr "<div class=\"tip\">\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p><i>Dangerzone</i> is created by <a href=\"https://freedom.press/\">Freedom of\n"
"the Press Foundation</a>, a nonprofit that protects public-interest\n"
"journalism. Edward Snowden and Laura Poitras are on its Board of Directors.</p>\n"
msgstr ""
"<p><i>Dangerzone</i> è realizzato da <a href=\"https://freedom.press/\">Freedom of\n"
"the Press Foundation</a>, è un'associazione senza scopo di lucro che tutela il giornalismo \n"
"di interesse pubblico. Edward Snowden e Laura Poitras fanno parte del Consiglio di amministrazione.</p>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "</div>\n"
msgstr "</div>\n"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"You can install *Dangerzone* in Tails using the [[Additional Software|"
"additional_software]] feature."
msgstr ""
"Puoi installare *Dangerzone* in Tails utilizzando la funzionalità [[Software "
"Aggiuntivo|additional_software]]."

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"We are not including *Dangerzone* in Tails only because it would be too big "
"(over 1 GB), but we highly recommend it."
msgstr ""
"Non includiamo *Dangerzone* in Tails solo perché sarebbe troppo pesante "
"(oltre 1 GB), ma lo consigliamo vivamente."

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Learn more about [how *Dangerzone* works](https://dangerzone.rocks/about/)."
msgstr ""
"Per saperne di più [su come funziona *Dangerzone*](https://dangerzone.rocks/"
"about/)."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[!toc levels=2]]\n"
msgstr "[[!toc levels=2]]\n"

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Supported formats"
msgstr "Formati compatibili"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Dangerzone* works on many file formats, including:\n"
msgstr "*Dangerzone* funziona su molti formati di file, tra cui:\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid "PDFs"
msgstr "PDF"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid "*Microsoft Office* documents, such as .docx, .xlsx, and .pptx"
msgstr "Documenti *Microsoft Office*, come .docx, .xlsx e .pptx"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid "*LibreOffice* documents, such as .odt and .ods"
msgstr "Documenti *LibreOffice*, come .odt and .ods"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid "Images, such as .jpg, .gif, .svg, .tiff, and .png"
msgstr "Immagini come .jpg, .gif, .svg, .tiff, and .png"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid "EPUB ebooks"
msgstr "Ebooks EPUB"

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Differences between *Dangerzone* and *Metadata Cleaner*"
msgstr "Differenze tra *Dangerzone* e *Metadata Cleaner*"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Tails also includes [[*Metadata Cleaner*|doc/sensitive_documents/metadata]] "
"to clean files, but the use cases for *Dangerzone* and *Metadata Cleaner* "
"are very different."
msgstr ""
"Tails include anche  [[*Metadata Cleaner*|doc/sensitive_documents/metadata]] "
"per la pulizia dei file, ma i casi d'uso di *Dangerzone* e *Metadata "
"Cleaner* sono molto diversi."

#. type: Plain text
msgid "We recommend that you use:"
msgstr "Ti consigliamo di usare:"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid ""
"*Metadata Cleaner* to [[remove metadata from your files|doc/"
"sensitive_documents/metadata]] before you publish or share them."
msgstr ""
"*Metadata Cleaner* per [[rimuovere i metadati dai file|sensitive_documents/"
"metadata]] prima di pubblicarli o condividerli."

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid "*Dangerzone* to sanitize untrusted documents shared with you by others."
msgstr ""
"*Dangerzone* per pulire i documenti non affidabili condivisi con altri."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<table>\n"
"<tr><th></th><th class=\"w30\">*Dangerzone*</th><th class=\"w30\">*Metadata Cleaner*</th></tr>\n"
"<tr><td>Safe to use on</td><td>Other people's files</td><td>Your files only</td></tr>\n"
"<tr><td>Clean audio and video files</td><td class=\"cross\">No</td><td class=\"check\">Yes</td></tr>\n"
"<tr><td>Remove malware and trackers</td><td class=\"check\">Yes</td><td class=\"cross\">No</td></tr>\n"
"<tr><td>Remove visual metadata and fingerprints¹</td><td class=\"cross\">No</td><td class=\"cross\">No</td></tr>\n"
"<tr><td>Allow selecting text in generated PDFs</td><td class=\"check\">Yes</td><td class=\"cross\">No</td></tr>\n"
"<tr><td>Speed</td><td class=\"cross\">Slower</td><td class=\"check\">Faster</td></tr>\n"
"<tr><td>Included in Tails by default</td><td class=\"cross\">No</td><td class=\"check\">Yes</td></tr>\n"
"</table>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1. For example [[!wikipedia Machine Identification Code desc=\"printer tracking\n"
"dots\"]], printing imperfections, or intentional misspellings\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "System requirements"
msgstr "Requisiti di sistema"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Dangerzone* requires a lot of memory in the computer and space in your\n"
"Persistent Storage because it relies on [[!wikipedia Containerization\n"
"(computing) desc=\"software containers\"]] to manipulate dangerous files\n"
"securely.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Dangerzone* richiede molta memoria del computer e spazio dell'\n"
"Archivio Persistente perché si basa sulla [[!wikipedia Containerization\n"
"(computing) desc=\"software containers\"]] per manipolare i file pericolosi\n"
"in modo sicuro.\n"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "To install *Dangerzone*, you need at least:"
msgstr "Per installare *Dangerzone*, sono necessari almeno:"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid "8 GB of RAM"
msgstr "8 GB di RAM"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid "12 GB available in the Persistent Storage"
msgstr "12 GB disponibili nell'Archivio Persistente"

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing *Dangerzone*"
msgstr "Installare *Dangerzone*"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "To install *Dangerzone* as additional software in Tails, you have to:"
msgstr ""
"Per installare *Dangerzone* come software aggiuntivo in Tails, è necessario:"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "[[Configure the *Dangerzone* APT repository|dangerzone#configure]]"
msgstr "[[Configurare il repository APT di *Dangerzone*|dangerzone#configure]]"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "[[Install the *Dangerzone* package|dangerzone#install]]"
msgstr "[[Installare il pacchetto *Dangerzone*|dangerzone#install]]"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "[[Convert a test document|dangerzone#test]]"
msgstr "[[Convertire un documento di prova|dangerzone#test]]"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<h2 id=\"configure\">Configure the <i>Dangerzone</i> APT repository</h2>\n"
msgstr "<h2 id=\"configure\">Configura <i>Dangerzone</i> repository APT</h2>\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"When starting Tails, [[set up an administration password|doc/first_steps/"
"welcome_screen/administration_password]]."
msgstr ""
"Quando avvii Tails, [[imposta una password di amministrazione|doc/"
"first_steps/welcome_screen/administration_password]]."

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Choose **Apps&nbsp;▸ Tails&nbsp;▸ Persistent Storage** to open the "
"Persistent Storage settings."
msgstr ""
"Scegli **App&nbsp;▸ Tails&nbsp;▸ Archiviazione persistente** per aprire le "
"impostazioni dell'Archivio Persistente."

#. type: Bullet: '   1. '
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "   Create a Persistent Storage if you don't have one already.\n"
msgid "Create a Persistent Storage if you don't have one already."
msgstr "   Crea un Archivio Persistente se non ne hai già uno.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '   1. '
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "   Make sure that the **Additional Software** feature is enabled.\n"
msgid "Make sure that the **Additional Software** feature is turned on."
msgstr ""
"   Assicurati che la funzionalità **Software Aggiuntivo** sia abilitata.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '   1. '
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "   Close the Persistent Storage settings.\n"
msgid "Close the Persistent Storage settings."
msgstr "   Chiudi le impostazioni dell'Archivio Persistente.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "Choose **Apps&nbsp;▸ System Tools&nbsp;▸ Console**."
msgstr "Scegli **App&nbsp;▸ Strumenti di sistema&nbsp;▸ Console**."

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Execute the following command to open the configuration of your Persistent "
"Storage in the *Text Editor* with administration rights."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "       gnome-text-editor admin:/live/persistence/TailsData_unlocked/persistence.conf\n"
msgstr "       gnome-text-editor admin:/live/persistence/TailsData_unlocked/persistence.conf\n"

#. type: Bullet: '   1. '
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "   Add the following line to store the configuration of third-party APT\n"
#| "   repositories in your Persistent Storage.\n"
msgid ""
"Add the following line to store the configuration of third-party APT "
"repositories in your Persistent Storage."
msgstr ""
"   Aggiungi la riga seguente per memorizzare la configurazione dei "
"repository APT\n"
"      di terze parti nell'Archivio Persistente.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "          /etc/apt/sources.list.d\tsource=apt/sources,link\n"
msgstr "          /etc/apt/sources.list.d\tsource=apt/sources,link\n"

#. type: Bullet: '   1. '
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "   Add the following line to store *Podman* containers in your "
#| "Persistent\n"
#| "   Storage. [*Podman*](https://podman.io/) is the containerization "
#| "technology\n"
#| "   used by *Dangerzone*.\n"
msgid ""
"Add the following line to store *Podman* containers in your Persistent "
"Storage. [*Podman*](https://podman.io/) is the containerization technology "
"used by *Dangerzone*."
msgstr ""
"   Aggiungi la seguente riga per memorizzare i contenitori *Podman* "
"nell'Archivio\n"
"      Persistente [*Podman*](https://podman.io/) è la tecnologia di "
"containerizzazione\n"
"       usata da *Dangerzone*.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "          /home/amnesia/.local/share/containers\tsource=podman\n"
msgstr "          /home/amnesia/.local/share/containers\tsource=podman\n"

#. type: Bullet: '   1. '
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "   Save your changes and close the *Text Editor*.\n"
msgid "Save your changes and close the *Text Editor*."
msgstr "   Salva le modifiche e chiudi l'Editor di testo.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Execute the following commands to configure the *Dangerzone* repository as "
"additional APT repository."
msgstr ""
"Esegui i seguenti comandi per configurare il repository *Dangerzone* come "
"repository APT aggiuntivo."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <p class=\"command\">sudo mkdir /live/persistence/TailsData_unlocked/apt/sources</p>\n"
msgstr "   <p class=\"command\">sudo mkdir /live/persistence/TailsData_unlocked/apt/sources</p>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <p class=\"command\">sudo ln -s /usr/share/tails/apt/dangerzone.sources /live/persistence/TailsData_unlocked/apt/sources/</p>\n"
msgstr "   <p class=\"command\">sudo ln -s /usr/share/tails/apt/dangerzone.sources /live/persistence/TailsData_unlocked/apt/sources/</p>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <div class=\"caution\">\n"
msgstr "   <div class=\"caution\">\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   <p>We include this sources file in Tails for convenience, but installing\n"
"   <i>Dangerzone</i> relies on the APT repository hosted by <a\n"
"   href=\"https://freedom.press/\">Freedom of the Press Foundation</a>.\n"
"   As a consequence:</p>\n"
msgstr ""
"   <p>Abbiamo incluso questo file di sorgenti in Tails per comodità, ma l'installazione di\n"
"      <i>Dangerzone</i> si basa sul repository APT ospitato da <a\n"
"      href=\"https://freedom.press/\">Freedom of the Press Foundation</a>.\n"
"      Di conseguenza:</p>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   <ul>\n"
"   <li>You need to trust the packages from this repository not to break the\n"
"   security of your Tails.</li>\n"
"   <li><i>Dangerzone</i> might stop working in Tails outside of the control of\n"
"   the Tails team.</li>\n"
"   </ul>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   </div>\n"
msgstr "   </div>\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "Restart Tails."
msgstr "Riavvia Tails."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<h2 id=\"install\">Install the <i>Dangerzone</i> package</h2>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "[[Connect to the Tor network.|doc/anonymous_internet/tor]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Execute the following commands to install the `dangerzone` package and its "
"dependencies."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <p class=\"command\">sudo apt update</p>\n"
msgstr "   <p class=\"command\">sudo apt update</p>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <p class=\"command\">sudo apt install dangerzone fuse-overlayfs uidmap</p>\n"
msgstr "   <p class=\"command\">sudo apt install dangerzone fuse-overlayfs uidmap</p>\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"After the packages are installed, a notification appears to ask if you want "
"to install `dangerzone`, `fuse-overlayfs`, and `uidmap` every time you start "
"Tails in the future."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   Choose to **Install Every Time**.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "Close the *Console*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<h2 id=\"test\">Convert a test document</h2>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "Choose **Apps&nbsp;▸ Office&nbsp;▸ Dangerzone** to open *Dangerzone*."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   When opened for the first time, *Dangerzone* installs its container.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   This operation can take several minutes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   After the setup finishes, *Dangerzone* opens.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   Click the button **Select suspicious documents**.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   [[!img dangerzone.png class=\"screenshot\" alt=\"\"]]\n"
msgstr "   [[!img dangerzone.png class=\"screenshot\" alt=\"\"]]\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Select a simple document to test the conversion process, like an empty "
"*LibreOffice* document or an image."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   Converting this first document can also take several minutes. After this\n"
"   first document, converting other documents will be faster.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <div class=\"bug\">\n"
msgstr "   <div class=\"bug\">\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   <p>If converting fails with the error <span class=\"code\">Unknown error code\n"
"   '125'</span>, restart Tails and try again.</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   <p><i>Dangerzone</i> needs a lot of available RAM when running for the first\n"
"   time. Restarting Tails frees as much RAM as possible.</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <p><i>Dangerzone</i> requires at least 8 GB of RAM to install.</p>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"After the conversion finishes, the original document is moved to a new "
"*unsafe* folder and the name of the safe document that has been created "
"includes *safe*. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"       ├── document-safe.odt\n"
"       └── unsafe\n"
"           └── document.odt\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<div class=\"next\">\n"
msgstr "<div class=\"next\">\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<p>You can use several applications included in Tails to [[edit the safe\n"
"PDF|sensitive_documents/pdf]] produced by <i>Dangerzone</i>.</p>\n"
msgstr ""
